				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\alpha _\nu $$\end{document} increases (compare K8, K8h, and K8s). Thus, accurate determination of the magnitude of the kinematic viscosity is important to predict quantitatively the amount of the disk outflow. Physically, it is necessary to clarify how the magnetorotational instability enhances the turbulence (see Sect. 3.5.3).Fig. 41
